    "Body": " Account Management is a critical function within the broader Customer Success organization. Ripple has more than 300 customers around the world with more being added every month. Engaging these customers so they become vibrant members of RippleNet is key to the company\u2019s future success. We seek an Account Manager based in our S?o Paulo, Brazil office to manage customer relationships within Brazil and elsewhere in South America. What You'll Do Develop a deep understanding of each customer\u2019s organization, internal constituents, aspirations and needs, identifying aspects of Ripple\u2019s engagement and advocacy that need to be strengthened Thoroughly understand the customer's appetite and key financial targets that can be addressed by Ripple (e.g., cost reduction, revenue growth, etc.) Through collaborating closely with Ripple Sales and Business Development teams, proactively develop and drive customers toward shared goals and targets Identify new business opportunities and develop prescriptive, strategic plans to transform our customers\u2019 businesses and drive platform adoption and transaction volume over RippleNet Oversee and drive customer-facing delivery responsibilities for both business and technical work-streams working closely with Ripple\u2019s Project Management team Lead hands-on, tactical task management to drive shared key initiatives and identify and creatively solve complex business and operational issues which may be inhibiting customer adoption and full utilization of Ripple Lead strong collaboration across virtual execution teams comprised of a broad, internal, cross-functional team (Product, Sales, Customer Success, Finance, Marketing and Legal) and our customers\u2019 project and business teams Build alignment among stakeholders and escalate key decisions as required through formal and informal communication Become a thought-leader among customers, enabling them to better exploit the potential of Ripple and participate in the development of new and ground-breaking applications Be the voice of Ripple\u2019s customers within the Ripple organization, ensuring that feedback and insights gained are properly disseminated, inculcated, and acted upon by Ripple Success Metrics Meet and exceed corridor build targets Meet and exceed targeted transaction volume for each customer Meet and exceed customer satisfaction and retention goals What We're Looking For Fluency in English, Spanish and Brazilian Portuguese 10+ years combined experience required in transaction banking, cash management, FX, payment processing, or a related field at a major financial institution in a customer-facing role Management consulting and delivery experience (or similar experience) gained within a technology or financial services organization Experience working in FinTech / Start-up organizations preferred Experience and cultural awareness with respect to working in and influencing cross-functional teams in a global enterprise Proven track record of implementing payment solutions within financial institutions Self-starter who is highly motivated to succeed in a challenging and rapidly changing business environment Results driven individual with determination and commitment to getting things done Ability and willingness to travel 30% or more of the time Ability to credibly communicate and influence at the leadership level Undergraduate degree or equivalent, MBA strongly preferred If you believe you are a strong fit for this role, please submit your English language resume for consideration. What We Offer The chance to work in a fast-paced start-up environment with experienced industry leaders A learning environment where you can dive deep into the latest technologies and make an impact Competitive salary and equity Health plans for employees and dependents Meal allowance Generous wellness reimbursement program Employee giving donation match Training in our Headquarters in San Francisco, CA, USA Weekly company meeting - ask me anything style discussions with our Leadership Team Who We Are Ripple provides one frictionless experience to send money globally using the power of blockchain. By joining Ripple\u2019s growing, global network (RippleNet), financial institutions can process their customers\u2019 payments anywhere in the world instantly, reliably and cost-effectively. Banks and payment providers can use the digital asset XRP to further reduce their costs and access new markets. With offices in San Francisco, New York, London, Mumbai, Singapore, S?o Paulo, Reykjav?k, Washington D.C. and Dubai, Ripple has more than 300 customers around the world. Ripple is an Equal Opportunity Employer. We\u2019re committed to building a diverse and inclusive team. We do not discriminate against qualified employees or applicants because of race, color, religion, gender identity, sex, sexual preference, sexual identity, pregnancy, national origin, ancestry, citizenship, age, marital status, physical disability, mental disability, medical condition, military status, or any other characteristic protected by local law or ordinance. Please find our UK/EU applicant privacy notice here. ", 
